<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>2 SPEED AXLE SHIFT UNIT: EATON - AIR SHIFT SYSTEM - AIR SHIFTER VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AIR SHIFTER VALVE</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove/Disassemble</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Air supply to valve must be shut off before valve is serviced.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>The shifter valve can be disassembled for service without removing the assembly from the gear shift
                lever.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screw from cover, then lift off cover and remove shifter knob, knob spring,
                    shifter plate, O-ring guide and O-ring from valve housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400230">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400230" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400230" filename="../figg14/G1400230.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 30. Air Shifter Valve Components</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If housing requires replacement, disconnect air lines, loosen jam nut, then unscrew
                    housing from shifter lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspect/Lubricate</title>
            <para>Each 50,000 miles, disassemble, inspect and clean, then lubricate moving parts with barium-base
                grease. No other type lubricant should be used.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Assemble/Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If housing was removed, install jam nut on shift lever. Thread housing on shift lever
                    and tighten jam nut. Connect air lines. Air shift valve knob should be positioned at 9 o'clock.
                    Lubricate moving parts with barium-base grease during assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place shifter plate in mounting position on valve housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400231">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400231" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400231" filename="../figg14/G1400231.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Shifter Valve Plate Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pre-assemble guide and O-ring, then place this assembly in mounting position in shifter
                    plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400232">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400232" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400232" filename="../figg14/G1400232.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 32. O-Ring and Guide Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold shifter plate in position with one hand, then install spring and shifter knob (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400233">Figure 33</hotlnk>). Install cover and fasten with screw.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400233" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400233" filename="../figg14/G1400233.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 33. Shifter Knob Installation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
